      "note": "Lit., \"or the heaven ...\", etc. The \"heaven\" is here, as in many other places in the Qur'an, a metonym for \"cosmic system\" (cf. note 20 on 2:29). The above verse is an echo of an earlier, more explicit passage - namely, 40:56-57, which should be read together with the corresponding notes 40 and 41. Both these passages refute the \"man-centred\" view of the universe by pointing out man's insignificance as compared with the vastness and complexity of the whole God-created universe."
